  <static seed="1180" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/multiplyRationalExpressions50.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r^{2}+3r-10}{r+4}} \cdot {\frac{2r+8}{r+5}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2\mathopen{}\left(r-2\right), r\ne -5\hbox{ and }r\ne -4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{r^{2}+3r-10}{r+4}} \cdot {\frac{2r+8}{r+5}} 
      \amp = \frac{{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-2\right)}}{{r+4}} \cdot \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}}{{r+5}} \\
      \amp = {2\mathopen{}\left(r-2\right), r\ne -5\hbox{ and }r\ne -4}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>r+5</m> and <m>r+4</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {-5, -4}</m>.</p>
</solution>
